author: CBS News
title: Bush's smiley face; Fiorina's jabs at low-energy debate rivals
text:
From the 2016 presidential candidates on Oct. 16, 2015: 
Jeb Bush on the set of "CBS This Morning" on Oct. 16, 2015. CBS News 

Jeb Bush: " :) " 
" CBS This Morning" questionnaire's fill-in-the-blank: "If I could ask one other candidate one question..."
Jeb Bush's handwritten response: "Why don't you like me? :)"
Former Hewlett-Packard CEO Carly Fiorina speaks at the Iowa Faith & Freedom 15th Annual Spring Kick Off, in Waukee, Iowa, Saturday, April 25, 2015. Nati Harnik, AP 

Carly Fiorina on Donald Trump and Ben Carson's demands for CNBC to limit debate time : 
"I think we need to be spend as much time as possible answering the American people's questions. I am all for three hours. I'm sorry if they apparently don't have the endurance to go the distance. I also think that prepared statements are something that politicians rely on. Let's take moderators questions and take as many of them as we can." -- at a campaign stop in Windsor, Iowa on October 15, 2015 
CBS News' Jean Song and Sean Gallitz contributed to this compilation.
